<Section>
	<Rubric>
		<Title>
			The Problem of Induction
		</Title>
	</Rubric>

	<Paragraph>
		Hume's argument against inductive reasoning remains one of the most
		persistent challenges in epistemology.
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		The core difficulty is that any justification for induction must itself rely
		on inductive reasoning, creating an unavoidable circularity.
	</Paragraph>
</Section>
